First Part – Project Background  
The provided contract, GuessTheRandomNumberChallenge, is a simple on-chain lottery-style puzzle. When deployed, it requires exactly 1 ETH as a deposit and immediately computes a “random” 8-bit answer by hashing the previous block’s blockhash and the current timestamp. Participants may later call the guess function—again sending exactly 1 ETH—to attempt to match that hidden answer. A correct guess pays out 2 ETH, draining the contract balance; an incorrect guess simply burns the sent ETH. The goal of the contract is to reward someone who successfully predicts the “random” number.

Second Part – Function Breakdown and Call Relationships  
Assuming the code is numbered as follows:
